body:
@blackdrag, @PascalSchumacher, @tkruse, @paulk-asert, @vladmm, @terebesirobert, please review :).
The original PR was pending for 1 year, I rebased it [upon request](https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/120#issuecomment-229251445).
Could we please review and merge this ASAP? (The [Java 7 node is building correctly](https://travis-ci.org/apache/groovy/jobs/141155143), the [Java 6 Travis node](https://travis-ci.org/apache/groovy/jobs/141155140) should be fixed...)

@tkruse which line are you worried about being "dodgy"?
The "ascending = ascendingStep" line?
That just covers the case when a single number will be selected and makes sure we don't head off in an infinite loop in the wrong direction.

@blackdrag, @tkruse, @paulk-asert, thanks for your comments, I removed the Number stepping commit and left all the refactorings.
If later someone decides to add the Number stepping, the code is easier to modify.

Let me know if the [last commit (the Number stepping optimization)](https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/360/commits/fbfb3621c85f988c25691036696541a2d9cfd16b) should be kept or removed.
